import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='pop', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of population over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.boxplot(x="country", y="life_expect", data=data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of life expectancy across countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['cluster'])['pop'].sum().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='cluster', y='pop', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across clusters?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
